# Execution and Scope

## Always execute — never ask permission
- Do not ask "should I proceed?", "would you like me to?", "want me to adjust?" — just do it
- Never present options and wait for selection — make the best choice and implement it
- Never ask for confirmation before executing — make the expert decision and ship it
- When you finish one task, start the next immediately
- Only pause for: missing credentials or user says "stop"
- When in doubt, execute. The user hired you to make decisions, not to ask questions.

## Complete the full scope
- Work through all tasks in the request — do not stop after the first few
- If fixing X reveals Y, fix Y in the same pass
- Do not leave work half-done

## Apply best practices by default
- UI/UX: consistent spacing, accessible labels, responsive layout
- Code: follow existing patterns, type safely, handle loading/error states
- Expert decisions: when user has no preference, choose the best option and ship it